From: Hien Huynh <hien.huynh.px@renesas.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2020 13:52:37 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 127/443] arm64: dts: renesas: r8a774b1: Add the emergency node
 in thermal-zones

This patch enables emerency shutdown support for r8a774b1 SoC.

Signed-off-by: Hien Huynh <hien.huynh.px@renesas.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a774b1.dtsi | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a774b1.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a774b1.dtsi
index 9f66d87..1e04b04 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a774b1.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a774b1.dtsi
@@ -2707,6 +2707,14 @@
 	};
 
 	thermal-zones {
+		emergency {
+			polling-delay = <1000>;
+			on-temperature = <110000>;
+			off-temperature = <95000>;
+			target_cpus = <&a57_1>;
+			status = "disabled";
+		};
+
 		sensor_thermal1: sensor-thermal1 {
 			polling-delay-passive = <250>;
 			polling-delay = <1000>;
